file=AI & Agents/gauge/logical/book-requirements.md · h=name: gauge-logical-book-requirements\ntype: logical\nstatus: built — fully covered by Shared OS inheritance (2026-07-15)\nassigned_agent: gauge (AI & Agents / Quality Benchmarks)\ndate_added: 2026-07-10\ndate_filled: 2026-07-15\n · p:=All logical scripts live in `Shared OS/logical/` (§13.5). Gauge is fully covered by inherited scripts. This file is the only file in this folder.\n · tb=\| Script \| Source Book \| Book URL \| Why Gauge Needs It \| · tb=\|--------\|------------\|----------\|---------------------\| · tb=\| `signal_detection.py` \| OpenStax Statistics 2e (2023) \| [openstax.org](https://openstax.org/) — FREE \| Control charts (Western Electric rules), drift detection replacing fixed ±20% thresholds, noise vs signal classification \| · tb=\| `experiment_methods.py` \| Kohavi et al. + OpenStax \| [experimentguide.com](https://experimentguide.com/) \| Sample size for golden-set calibration, power analysis for benchmark significance \| · tb=\| `fleet_measurement.py` \| DeMarco (1982) + CETIC \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/) — FREE \| Fleet health composite for overall quality benchmark \| · tb=\| Previously Flagged (0.6) \| Status \| Script \| · tb=\|--------------------------\|--------\|--------\| · tb=\| Control limits instead of fixed ±20% drift \| ✅ Cleared \| `signal_detection.py` (control_limits, check_western_electric_rules) \| · tb=\| Distinguishing noise from signal in small task counts \| ✅ Cleared \| `signal_detection.py` (classify_metric_change — checks sample size, normality, CI overlap, significance) \| · tb=\| Golden-set sample sizes \| ✅ Cleared \| `experiment_methods.py` (mde_to_sample_size, experiment_power) \| · sm:=- **scorecard** → imports `signal_detection.py` (control_limits, detect_metric_drift) + `experiment_methods.py` (MDE)\n